The ideal heart valve substitute would show no deterioration or thrombogenicity, 
offer no resistance to blood flow, and be easy to implant. However, such a valve 
does not exist and we must accept compromises in some of these qualities based 
on our patients' needs. In selection of cardiac valve prosthesis, valve-related 
factors such as durability, thrombogenicity, and fluid dynamics should be 
carefully matched to patient-related factors such as age, size, life expectancy, 
comorbidities, plans for pregnancy, and lifestyle. In addition, surgeon- or 
